{
  "texts": [
    "Post-processing.Post-processing encompasses a series of automated procedures designed to transform the initial output of LLMs into executable, high-quality code.Validation and Repair.",
    "Validation and repair are pivotal components of post-processing.",
    "Mainstream frameworks (e.g., CasModaTest [99], ChatUniTest [27], TestSpark [120]) widely adopt an iterative \"generate-validate-repair\" loop by capturing error messages from the compilation or execution stages and providing them as feedback to the LLM for self-correction.",
    "Empirical studies indicate that this mechanism significantly improves the pass rate of test cases [56,99].",
    "Complementing iterative repair, automatic validity prediction and correction (e.g., VALTEST) utilize token probability features to pre-filter low-quality tests and employ CoT to repair them [131]."
  ]
}